column3: Do we have a mechanism for dead code detection?
Please include in what commit it was last used.
utACK c6d4a81.\n\ngrepped codebase for `Find(`. Other instances found are `CAddrMan::Find` and `FindFileTest::Find` in leveldb.
The test failure is known issue #12863

NACK 8cbc5c4be4be22aca228074f087a374a7ec38be8 -- code is fine, but it introduces a merge conflict with #12885 due to being adjacent in the file being patched, so this should be rebased after that is merged IMO.

utACK 8cbc5c4be4be22aca228074f087a374a7ec38be8

I don't see any `Find(…)` usage being removed in 922e8e2?

My reading is that `Find(…)` has been unused since being introduced in e679ec969c8b22c676ebb10bea1038f6c8f13b33.

Anyways – nice find!

_Edit: Found the removed usage. GitHub's interface tricked me :-)_

@practicalswift  There's `subscript.Find(OP_CODESEPERATOR)`,  `scriptPubKey.Find(OP_EVAL)` and `scriptSig.Find(OP_EVAL)` removed in that commit. Github hides them with a "Large diffs are not rendered by default." though.\n
Drop dead, code! utACK 8cbc5c4be4be22aca228074f087a374a7ec38be8\n\n@ajtowns I'll gladly rebase #12885 if this is merged first.
